  "question": [
    "A radioactive sample has half-life of 3 years. The time required for the activity of the sample to reduce to $\\frac{1}{5}$ th of its initial value is about"
  ],
  "choices": [
    [
      "15 years"
    ],
    [
      "5 years"
    ],
    [
      "10 years"
    ],
    [
      "7 years"
    ]
  ],
  "correctAnswer": 2,
  "explanation": [
    "Using $N/N_0 = (1/2)^n$, $1/5 = (1/2)^{t/3}$.",
    "$2^{t/3} = 5 \\Rightarrow t/3 \\ln 2 = \\ln 5$.",
    "$t = 3 \\times (\\ln 5 / \\ln 2) \\approx 3 \\times 2.32 = 6.96$ years."
  ],
  "years": [
    2023
  ]
}